## Phase 3: Add Rate Limit Status to Admin Logs

Optionally, log rate limit blocks as admin-visible events. Add this to [server.py](file:///c:/BatchHost-Pro/server.py) inside `log_request_info()` at [line 94](file:///c:/BatchHost-Pro/server.py#L94):

```diff
 @app.before_request
 def log_request_info():
     g.start_time = time.time()
     if request.path.startswith('/images') or request.path.startswith('/static'):
         return
     logging.info(f"Incoming request: {request.method} {request.path} from {request.remote_addr}")
     if request.is_json and request.json:
         safe_data = {k: v for k, v in request.json.items() if 'password' not in k.lower()}
         logging.info(f"Request payload: {json.dumps(safe_data)}")
```

The rate limit decorator already logs blocks via `logging.warning()`, so they will appear in [server.log](file:///c:/BatchHost-Pro/logs/server.log). No additional changes are required.

